[{"categories":["Api"],"date":"2024-12-24T00:00:00Z","id":"/posts/what-is-api/","keywords":[],"summary":"\u003ch3 id=\"what-is-an-api\" class=\"scroll-mt-8 group\"\u003e\n  What is an API?\n  \n    \u003ca href=\"#what-is-an-api\"\n        class=\"no-underline hidden opacity-50 hover:opacity-100 !text-inherit group-hover:inline-block\"\n        aria-hidden=\"true\" title=\"Link to this heading\" tabindex=\"-1\"\u003e\n        \u003csvg\n  xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"\n  width=\"16\"\n  height=\"16\"\n  fill=\"none\"\n  stroke=\"currentColor\"\n  stroke-linecap=\"round\"\n  stroke-linejoin=\"round\"\n  stroke-width=\"2\"\n  class=\"lucide lucide-link w-4 h-4 block\"\n  viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"\n\u003e\n  \u003cpath d=\"M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71\" /\u003e\n  \u003cpath d=\"M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71\" /\u003e\n\u003c/svg\u003e\n\n    \u003c/a\u003e\n  \n\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAn API (Application Programming Interface) is a tool that allows different software applications to communicate with each other. Think of it as a bridge that connects systems, enabling them to share data and perform tasks without knowing the details of how the other system works.\u003c/p\u003e","tags":[],"title":"What is API?"},{"categories":["Maven"],"date":"2024-12-15T00:00:00Z","id":"/posts/maven-achetypes/","keywords":[],"summary":"\u003cp\u003eMaven archetypes are templates that help developers quickly set up a new project with a predefined structure and files. Using an archetype, you can create a Maven project that already includes the necessary folders, configurations, and code for a specific type of application.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch3 id=\"how-maven-archetypes-work\" class=\"scroll-mt-8 group\"\u003e\n  How Maven Archetypes Work\n  \n    \u003ca href=\"#how-maven-archetypes-work\"\n        class=\"no-underline hidden opacity-50 hover:opacity-100 !text-inherit group-hover:inline-block\"\n        aria-hidden=\"true\" title=\"Link to this heading\" tabindex=\"-1\"\u003e\n        \u003csvg\n  xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"\n  width=\"16\"\n  height=\"16\"\n  fill=\"none\"\n  stroke=\"currentColor\"\n  stroke-linecap=\"round\"\n  stroke-linejoin=\"round\"\n  stroke-width=\"2\"\n  class=\"lucide lucide-link w-4 h-4 block\"\n  viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"\n\u003e\n  \u003cpath d=\"M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71\" /\u003e\n  \u003cpath d=\"M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71\" /\u003e\n\u003c/svg\u003e\n\n    \u003c/a\u003e\n  \n\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eArchetypes act as \u0026ldquo;project blueprints,\u0026rdquo; saving time and ensuring consistency across projects.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eWhen creating a new project, you select an archetype, and Maven generates a ready-to-use project structure.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eYou can also customize the generated project by providing specific details, like the group ID, artifact ID, and version.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003ch3 id=\"two-popular-archetype-examples\" class=\"scroll-mt-8 group\"\u003e\n  Two Popular Archetype Examples\n  \n    \u003ca href=\"#two-popular-archetype-examples\"\n        class=\"no-underline hidden opacity-50 hover:opacity-100 !text-inherit group-hover:inline-block\"\n        aria-hidden=\"true\" title=\"Link to this heading\" tabindex=\"-1\"\u003e\n        \u003csvg\n  xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"\n  width=\"16\"\n  height=\"16\"\n  fill=\"none\"\n  stroke=\"currentColor\"\n  stroke-linecap=\"round\"\n  stroke-linejoin=\"round\"\n  stroke-width=\"2\"\n  class=\"lucide lucide-link w-4 h-4 block\"\n  viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"\n\u003e\n  \u003cpath d=\"M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71\" /\u003e\n  \u003cpath d=\"M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71\" /\u003e\n\u003c/svg\u003e\n\n    \u003c/a\u003e\n  \n\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003ch4 id=\"maven-archetype-quickstart\" class=\"scroll-mt-8 group\"\u003e\n  maven-archetype-quickstart\n  \n    \u003ca href=\"#maven-archetype-quickstart\"\n        class=\"no-underline hidden opacity-50 hover:opacity-100 !text-inherit group-hover:inline-block\"\n        aria-hidden=\"true\" title=\"Link to this heading\" tabindex=\"-1\"\u003e\n        \u003csvg\n  xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"\n  width=\"16\"\n  height=\"16\"\n  fill=\"none\"\n  stroke=\"currentColor\"\n  stroke-linecap=\"round\"\n  stroke-linejoin=\"round\"\n  stroke-width=\"2\"\n  class=\"lucide lucide-link w-4 h-4 block\"\n  viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"\n\u003e\n  \u003cpath d=\"M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71\" /\u003e\n  \u003cpath d=\"M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71\" /\u003e\n\u003c/svg\u003e\n\n    \u003c/a\u003e\n  \n\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eIdeal for setting up a basic Java project.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eIncludes a standard directory structure (src/main/java, src/test/java) and a simple App.java file with a main method.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003ePerfect for beginners or small projects where no specific framework is required.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003ch4 id=\"maven-archetype-webapp\" class=\"scroll-mt-8 group\"\u003e\n  maven-archetype-webapp\n  \n    \u003ca href=\"#maven-archetype-webapp\"\n        class=\"no-underline hidden opacity-50 hover:opacity-100 !text-inherit group-hover:inline-block\"\n        aria-hidden=\"true\" title=\"Link to this heading\" tabindex=\"-1\"\u003e\n        \u003csvg\n  xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"\n  width=\"16\"\n  height=\"16\"\n  fill=\"none\"\n  stroke=\"currentColor\"\n  stroke-linecap=\"round\"\n  stroke-linejoin=\"round\"\n  stroke-width=\"2\"\n  class=\"lucide lucide-link w-4 h-4 block\"\n  viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"\n\u003e\n  \u003cpath d=\"M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71\" /\u003e\n  \u003cpath d=\"M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71\" /\u003e\n\u003c/svg\u003e\n\n    \u003c/a\u003e\n  \n\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eUsed to create a basic Java web application.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eIncludes a default structure for web development (e.g., src/main/webapp for web files like HTML, CSS, and JSP).\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eSets up essential files like web.xml for deploying the application on a servlet container like Tomcat.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003ch3 id=\"how-to-create-a-spring-application-using-maven-archetypes\" class=\"scroll-mt-8 group\"\u003e\n  How to Create a Spring Application Using Maven Archetypes\n  \n    \u003ca href=\"#how-to-create-a-spring-application-using-maven-archetypes\"\n        class=\"no-underline hidden opacity-50 hover:opacity-100 !text-inherit group-hover:inline-block\"\n        aria-hidden=\"true\" title=\"Link to this heading\" tabindex=\"-1\"\u003e\n        \u003csvg\n  xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"\n  width=\"16\"\n  height=\"16\"\n  fill=\"none\"\n  stroke=\"currentColor\"\n  stroke-linecap=\"round\"\n  stroke-linejoin=\"round\"\n  stroke-width=\"2\"\n  class=\"lucide lucide-link w-4 h-4 block\"\n  viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"\n\u003e\n  \u003cpath d=\"M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71\" /\u003e\n  \u003cpath d=\"M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71\" /\u003e\n\u003c/svg\u003e\n\n    \u003c/a\u003e\n  \n\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eGenerate the Project with Maven Quickstart Archetype Run the following command in your terminal:\u003c/p\u003e","tags":[],"title":"Maven archetypes"},{"categories":["Testing"],"date":"2024-12-15T00:00:00Z","id":"/posts/testcontainers-docker-compose-module/","keywords":[],"summary":"\u003cp\u003eUsing \u003cstrong\u003eDocker Compose module\u003c/strong\u003e with Testcontainers you can simplify testing for applications that rely on multiple services like:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eDatabases\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAPIs\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMessage queues\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis approach ensures that all dependencies start and work together as expected in a controlled, reproducible environment during your Java tests.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch3 id=\"key-features-of-the-docker-compose-module\" class=\"scroll-mt-8 group\"\u003e\n  Key features of the Docker Compose module\n  \n    \u003ca href=\"#key-features-of-the-docker-compose-module\"\n        class=\"no-underline hidden opacity-50 hover:opacity-100 !text-inherit group-hover:inline-block\"\n        aria-hidden=\"true\" title=\"Link to this heading\" tabindex=\"-1\"\u003e\n        \u003csvg\n  xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"\n  width=\"16\"\n  height=\"16\"\n  fill=\"none\"\n  stroke=\"currentColor\"\n  stroke-linecap=\"round\"\n  stroke-linejoin=\"round\"\n  stroke-width=\"2\"\n  class=\"lucide lucide-link w-4 h-4 block\"\n  viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"\n\u003e\n  \u003cpath d=\"M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71\" /\u003e\n  \u003cpath d=\"M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71\" /\u003e\n\u003c/svg\u003e\n\n    \u003c/a\u003e\n  \n\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eIt allows you to define complex service dependencies in a single docker-compose.yml file.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eDuring tests, Testcontainers can automatically start all services defined in the Compose file.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eIt ensures your test environment is isolated and reproducible.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eThe module also provides Java APIs to control the containers and check their status during tests.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003ch3 id=\"how-to-use-the-docker-compose-module\" class=\"scroll-mt-8 group\"\u003e\n  How to use the Docker Compose module\n  \n    \u003ca href=\"#how-to-use-the-docker-compose-module\"\n        class=\"no-underline hidden opacity-50 hover:opacity-100 !text-inherit group-hover:inline-block\"\n        aria-hidden=\"true\" title=\"Link to this heading\" tabindex=\"-1\"\u003e\n        \u003csvg\n  xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"\n  width=\"16\"\n  height=\"16\"\n  fill=\"none\"\n  stroke=\"currentColor\"\n  stroke-linecap=\"round\"\n  stroke-linejoin=\"round\"\n  stroke-width=\"2\"\n  class=\"lucide lucide-link w-4 h-4 block\"\n  viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"\n\u003e\n  \u003cpath d=\"M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71\" /\u003e\n  \u003cpath d=\"M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71\" /\u003e\n\u003c/svg\u003e\n\n    \u003c/a\u003e\n  \n\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003ch4 id=\"add-testcontainers-dependency\" class=\"scroll-mt-8 group\"\u003e\n  Add Testcontainers Dependency\n  \n    \u003ca href=\"#add-testcontainers-dependency\"\n        class=\"no-underline hidden opacity-50 hover:opacity-100 !text-inherit group-hover:inline-block\"\n        aria-hidden=\"true\" title=\"Link to this heading\" tabindex=\"-1\"\u003e\n        \u003csvg\n  xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"\n  width=\"16\"\n  height=\"16\"\n  fill=\"none\"\n  stroke=\"currentColor\"\n  stroke-linecap=\"round\"\n  stroke-linejoin=\"round\"\n  stroke-width=\"2\"\n  class=\"lucide lucide-link w-4 h-4 block\"\n  viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"\n\u003e\n  \u003cpath d=\"M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71\" /\u003e\n  \u003cpath d=\"M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71\" /\u003e\n\u003c/svg\u003e\n\n    \u003c/a\u003e\n  \n\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eInclude the Testcontainers library in your pom.xml (for Maven) or build.gradle (for Gradle):\u003c/p\u003e","tags":[],"title":"Testcontainers Docker Compose module"},{"categories":["Search"],"date":"2024-12-13T00:00:00Z","id":"/posts/job-vacancies-search/","keywords":[],"summary":"\u003cp\u003eYou can use advanced Google search queries to find job vacancies on LinkedIn that match specific roles and include details about visa sponsorship or relocation support. Here’s how the provided links work:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch3 id=\"1-broad-search-query\" class=\"scroll-mt-8 group\"\u003e\n  1. Broad Search Query\n  \n    \u003ca href=\"#1-broad-search-query\"\n        class=\"no-underline hidden opacity-50 hover:opacity-100 !text-inherit group-hover:inline-block\"\n        aria-hidden=\"true\" title=\"Link to this heading\" tabindex=\"-1\"\u003e\n        \u003csvg\n  xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"\n  width=\"16\"\n  height=\"16\"\n  fill=\"none\"\n  stroke=\"currentColor\"\n  stroke-linecap=\"round\"\n  stroke-linejoin=\"round\"\n  stroke-width=\"2\"\n  class=\"lucide lucide-link w-4 h-4 block\"\n  viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"\n\u003e\n  \u003cpath d=\"M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71\" /\u003e\n  \u003cpath d=\"M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71\" /\u003e\n\u003c/svg\u003e\n\n    \u003c/a\u003e\n  \n\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe first link is a general Google search query that looks for jobs with titles like\u003c/p\u003e","tags":[],"title":"Searching LinkedIn vacancies using Google"},{"categories":["Spring","Testing"],"date":"2024-12-04T00:00:00Z","id":"/posts/standalone-spring-tests/","keywords":[],"summary":"\u003cp\u003eI was surprised that Spring Test library doesn\u0026rsquo;t support standalone acceptance tests format out of the box.\nHere\u0026rsquo;s how I tackled this issue and why standalone tests are useful for modular Spring applications.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch3 id=\"motivation\" class=\"scroll-mt-8 group\"\u003e\n  Motivation\n  \n    \u003ca href=\"#motivation\"\n        class=\"no-underline hidden opacity-50 hover:opacity-100 !text-inherit group-hover:inline-block\"\n        aria-hidden=\"true\" title=\"Link to this heading\" tabindex=\"-1\"\u003e\n        \u003csvg\n  xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"\n  width=\"16\"\n  height=\"16\"\n  fill=\"none\"\n  stroke=\"currentColor\"\n  stroke-linecap=\"round\"\n  stroke-linejoin=\"round\"\n  stroke-width=\"2\"\n  class=\"lucide lucide-link w-4 h-4 block\"\n  viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"\n\u003e\n  \u003cpath d=\"M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71\" /\u003e\n  \u003cpath d=\"M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71\" /\u003e\n\u003c/svg\u003e\n\n    \u003c/a\u003e\n  \n\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eMy project separates core logic from cloud-specific modules. Usual Spring Test doesn\u0026rsquo;t work for this. I needed standalone tests to validate HTTP status codes and response content as black-box tests.\u003c/p\u003e","tags":[],"title":"Standalone Spring tests"},{"categories":["Money"],"date":"2024-12-02T00:00:00Z","id":"/posts/where-is-all-the-money-in-the-world/","keywords":[],"summary":"\u003ch3 id=\"overview-of-the-global-money-supply\" class=\"scroll-mt-8 group\"\u003e\n  Overview of the global money supply\n  \n    \u003ca href=\"#overview-of-the-global-money-supply\"\n        class=\"no-underline hidden opacity-50 hover:opacity-100 !text-inherit group-hover:inline-block\"\n        aria-hidden=\"true\" title=\"Link to this heading\" tabindex=\"-1\"\u003e\n        \u003csvg\n  xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"\n  width=\"16\"\n  height=\"16\"\n  fill=\"none\"\n  stroke=\"currentColor\"\n  stroke-linecap=\"round\"\n  stroke-linejoin=\"round\"\n  stroke-width=\"2\"\n  class=\"lucide lucide-link w-4 h-4 block\"\n  viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"\n\u003e\n  \u003cpath d=\"M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71\" /\u003e\n  \u003cpath d=\"M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71\" /\u003e\n\u003c/svg\u003e\n\n    \u003c/a\u003e\n  \n\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eMoney is the lifeblood of the global economy, flowing through various sectors, industries, and institutions. Understanding where money is located provides valuable insights into the structure of the global economy, wealth distribution, and financial trends. In 2023, the global money supply is spread across financial institutions, governments, businesses, and households, reflecting diverse economic activities.\u003c/p\u003e","tags":[],"title":"Where is all the money in the world?"},{"categories":["Websites"],"date":"2024-12-01T00:00:00Z","id":"/posts/static-site-generators/","keywords":[],"summary":"\u003ch3 id=\"overview-of-the-top-6-static-site-generators\" class=\"scroll-mt-8 group\"\u003e\n  Overview of the top 6 static site generators\n  \n    \u003ca href=\"#overview-of-the-top-6-static-site-generators\"\n        class=\"no-underline hidden opacity-50 hover:opacity-100 !text-inherit group-hover:inline-block\"\n        aria-hidden=\"true\" title=\"Link to this heading\" tabindex=\"-1\"\u003e\n        \u003csvg\n  xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"\n  width=\"16\"\n  height=\"16\"\n  fill=\"none\"\n  stroke=\"currentColor\"\n  stroke-linecap=\"round\"\n  stroke-linejoin=\"round\"\n  stroke-width=\"2\"\n  class=\"lucide lucide-link w-4 h-4 block\"\n  viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"\n\u003e\n  \u003cpath d=\"M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71\" /\u003e\n  \u003cpath d=\"M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71\" /\u003e\n\u003c/svg\u003e\n\n    \u003c/a\u003e\n  \n\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eStatic site generators are tools that create websites by converting templates and content into static HTML files.\nThis approach makes websites faster, more secure, and easier to host.\nLet’s take a closer look at six popular static site generators:\u003c/p\u003e","tags":[],"title":"Static site generators"}]
